        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:44PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wolf Creek Park, or 15 miles southeast of Perryton, moving north at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Booker and Wolf Creek Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
